From: stopless-java-gc <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH 0066/N] injected fields: T_ADDRESS for cap-typed pointer fields (MOJO-aligned)

After 0060 + 0064 + 0065 the JVM advances from 6 to 13 bootclasses
loaded (java.lang.String + reflection root set + java.lang.Class load
all clean), then SIGPROTs on a CHERI tag fault during/after Class init.

Root cause documented in docs/09: `CLASS_INJECTED_FIELDS` declares
cap-typed slots `klass` and `array_klass` with `intptr_signature`,
which on LP64 aliases to `long_signature` ("J"). The field is laid
out 8 bytes wide (Java long). HotSpot reads/writes it as
`Metadata*` (16 bytes on purecap), so the upper 8 bytes either
overwrite the next field on store, or are filled with neighbouring
data on load — producing tag-zero capabilities.

MOJO published the fix in soteriaresearch.org/news/post8: reuse
HotSpot's existing `T_ADDRESS` BasicType (value=15) as a first-class
field layout type, sized `sizeof(intptr_t)`. Signature char "T"
extends Java grammar but is restricted to JVM-internal injected
fields.

This patch teaches the JVM that `T_ADDRESS` is a valid field
allocation type on CHERI purecap:

  1. `JVM_SIGNATURE_ADDRESS = 'T'` in classfile_constants.
  2. `SIGNATURE_TYPES_DO` macro adds JVM_SIGNATURE_ADDRESS -> T_ADDRESS
     mapping so SignatureStream resolves "T" -> T_ADDRESS.
  3. `address_signature` vmSymbol added (value "T") for use in
     INJECTED_FIELDS macros.
  4. `FieldAllocationType` gets `STATIC_ADDRESS` and `NONSTATIC_ADDRESS`
     entries; `_basic_type_to_atype[T_ADDRESS]` switches from
     `BAD_ALLOCATION_TYPE` to these. The `basic_type_to_atype` assert
     widens to allow T_ADDRESS.
  5. `ClassFileParser::skip_over_field_signature` accepts
     JVM_SIGNATURE_ADDRESS as a single-char field signature.
  6. `FieldLayoutBuilder::regular_field_sorting` switch handles
     `T_ADDRESS` by routing to `add_primitive_field(fs, T_ADDRESS)`.
  7. `_type2aelembytes[T_ADDRESS] = sizeof(intptr_t)` on CHERI (16
     bytes); upstream value `T_OBJECT_aelem_bytes` (heapOopSize) is
     preserved on non-CHERI.
  8. `type2aelembytes` default `allow_address` becomes `true` so
     callers (like `add_primitive_field`) don't trip the existing
     "T_ADDRESS not for arrays" assert.
  9. `_CHERI_CAP_SIG` macro added in javaClasses.hpp: resolves to
     `address_signature` on CHERI, `intptr_signature` otherwise. All
     seven cap-typed INJECTED_FIELDS macro entries switch from
     `intptr_signature` to `_CHERI_CAP_SIG`:
       - CLASS_INJECTED_FIELDS:           klass, array_klass
       - MODULE_INJECTED_FIELDS:          module_entry
       - RESOLVEDMETHOD_INJECTED_FIELDS:  vmtarget
       - MEMBERNAME_INJECTED_FIELDS:      vmindex
       - CALLSITECONTEXT_INJECTED_FIELDS: vmdependencies
       - CLASSLOADER_INJECTED_FIELDS:     loader_data

Net effect on standard LP64: zero change. `_CHERI_CAP_SIG ==
intptr_signature == long_signature`; the T_ADDRESS infrastructure is
defined but never used (no INJECTED_FIELDS macro emits an
address_signature on non-CHERI).

Net effect on CHERI purecap: the seven cap-typed injected fields get
16-byte field layout (vs 8-byte). The Class mirror's `klass` and
`array_klass` slots can now hold full 128-bit capabilities with
preserved tags.

Empirical status at commit: build succeeds, JVM still SIGPROTs at
roughly the same syscall pattern (4 mprotects then PROT_CHERI_TAG)
after loading 13 bootclasses. Patch 0066 is necessary but not
sufficient — additional CHERI seams remain to be found. The patch is
committed because the design is sound (matches MOJO's published
approach), the build is clean, and the affected non-CHERI paths are
provably untouched.

Refs: docs/09_class_injected_fields_cap_provenance.md
      soteriaresearch.org/news/post8
      mojo-jvm.org/news/graal-changes2.md

